-- Taiwan Stocks: Largan, Novatek Microelectronics, Powertech
-- B y   W e i y i   L i m
-- 2012-02-10T05:53:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-10/taiwan-stocks-largan-precision-novatek-micro-pegatron-corp-.html
Shares of the following companies
had  unusual  moves in  Taiwan trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in Taipei.  The Taiex Index fell 0.6 percent to 7,862.27, snapping
three days of gains. The benchmark index increased 1.6 percent
this week, a fifth consecutive weekly advance.  Largan Precision Co. (3008)  (3008 TT) slid 6.9 percent to NT$638,
the biggest drop since Nov. 24. The lensmaker’s rating was cut
to “sell” from “buy” at Citigroup Inc. and lowered to
“hold” from “buy” at Yuanta Securities Co.  Novatek Microelectronics Corp. (3034)  (3034 TT) slumped 7 percent
to NT$85.70, the biggest drop since May 26, 2009. The integrated
circuit maker was cut to “hold” from “buy” at Deutsche Bank
AG.  Powertech Technology Inc. (6239)  (6239 TT), an integrated circuit
maker, sank 6.9 percent to NT$75.20, the biggest loss since Aug.
5. The stock was cut to “sell” from “buy” at Citigroup and
lowered to “neutral” at Credit Suisse Group AG.  To contact the reporter on this story:
